I don't know anything available about databases. We'll be glad to get what
you will do or get from others.

Concerning introductory courses for Caml, we have several books
available, but they are all written in french:

Introductory course for Caml programming:
  Le langage Caml, Pierre Weis et Xavier Leroy (InterEditions 1993).

Manual:
  Manuel de Reference du langage Caml, Xavier Leroy et Pierre Weis
  (InterEditions 1993)

Introductory course to programming using Caml and Ada:
Concepts et outils de programmation
le style fonctionnel, le style imperatif
avec CAML et Ada

Auteurs: Therese Accart Hardin et Veronique Donzeau-Gouge Viguie
(InterEditions 1991)

And of course you have the english documentation for Caml Light, freely
available by anonymous ftp:
  Functional programming in Caml Light by Michel Mauny
  Reference Manual, by Xavier Leroy.

Hope this helps,

Pierre Weis
